      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a home in Toronto, is a trust account that holds funds for various expenses associated with the transaction. It's a necessary step to ensure that the seller receives the full payment for the property at closing, and that you receive the keys to the house. The escrow account typically holds funds for property taxes, insurance, and any other costs associated with the property, which are usually paid out of the escrow account on a regular basis. This way, you can budget for these expenses, and the seller receives the full payment upfront, without having to worry about these costs being deducted later on.",
